The 1st column gives an overview of all the tags and

The second column shows all the papers, sorted
by date. The list is reduced when a filter is
applied, or when the search bar is used.
The third column shows the selected paper
(on startup, the most recent). On smaller screens,
only a fraction of the width of the page may be visible.

Animation: the view selector slides up to the new document, and a scan button is revealed from behind the left headerbar.
The "+" button turns insensitive, as well as the 3 buttons at the right of the headerbar.
The "+" button reveals a popover to select from which source the document should be created.

The item is updated with another tip. The scan button turns into a progress bar, and a stop button is available next to it.
An overlay gives information about the current page. Prev/Next buttons are insensitive.
Animation: Paperwork guesses the orientation of the page, the documents list slides out to give some room to the
information panel, which slides in. No need to wait for this to complete to start scanning the next page.
Once the page is ready, controls appear in overlay to manipulate it. The information panel slides in from the right, so the
user can fill in information about the document.
After pressing the "i" button, the information panel slides out. The document list slides in back.
The overlay fades out when if there has been no interaction with the page.

text.tspan: A blue disc appears in the export button
to notify there is a queue pending.
The queue allows to export a bunch of papers,
as well as pages picked up from here and there, all at once.
The expand buttons shows the pages to be exported
Clicking the page number selects it in the reader,
If the user realizes she is actually not interested with this page,
she can remove it from the queue.
It is possible to send documents to a queue,
from a dropdown menu in the document list.
Single pages can be sent to the queue the same way papers are,
using overlaid controls (visible after scan and while scrolling).
The "export" button reveals a popover allowing
to export the current document by different manners.
